---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Missile Squad Building" 
  description="Missile squad building guide for Last War: Survival."
>
  <h1>Missile Squad Building</h1>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p>Missile is a high-damage type that shines against certain compositions. It is often the third squad type players build once they have a strong foundation in Tank or Aircraft.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Hero Focus Order (Mid-Game Guidance)</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Priorities shift by season. Focus on building a core that can output consistent damage while surviving long enough to matter.</p>

  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Priority</th>
          <th>Hero</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold text-[#f59e0b]">1</td>
          <td><strong>Tesla</strong></td>
          <td>Frequently the top priority Missile DPS. Strong single-target and AoE potential.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">2</td>
          <td><strong>Swift</strong></td>
          <td>Excellent damage and utility. High priority for most Missile builds.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">3</td>
          <td><strong>McGregor</strong></td>
          <td>Solid frontline or support option that enables the backline to perform.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">4</td>
          <td><strong>Support / Flex</strong></td>
          <td>Heroes that provide buffs, crowd control, or secondary damage.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Positioning Notes</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Missile squads often benefit from specific formations that protect key damage dealers while using tankier units to absorb pressure. Experiment with in-game tools and adjust based on common enemy lineups on your server.</p>

  <h2>Progression Advice</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Prioritize stars on your top 1–2 DPS heroes (commonly Tesla/Swift).</li>
    <li>Build supporting units that enable your main damage dealers.</li>
    <li>Missile is usually more effective once you have decent gear and research supporting it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Visual Guides</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Community-created Missile squad references (including Aethernis-style layouts with hero order, skills, and prioritization) are available on Reddit and other platforms.</p>

  <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-[#1a253f] border border-[#f59e0b]/30 rounded">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Support Aethernis’ work:</strong> <a href="https://ko-fi.com/aethernis" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b]">ko-fi.com/aethernis</a></p>
    <p class="text-xs text-[#8a96b0] mt-1">Search for “Aethernis Missile squad guide” for detailed visual references.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <a href="/squad-building" class="text-[#f59e0b]">← Back to Squad Building Principles</a>
  </div>
</Layout>